All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Appointment
    Represents an appointment associated with a user, contact, and customer
    AppointmentController
    Controls and populates the appointments view, the edit appointments view, and the add appointments view
    Contact
    Represents a contact with an id, name, and email
    ContactController
    Gets contacts from database, stores allContacts observable array
    Customer
    Represents a customer, has many appointments
    CustomerController
    Controls and populates the customers view, the edit customers view, and the add customers view
    Division
    Represents a division, has an id, country, and division (string, not class)
    Helper
    Connects to and queries database, throws alerts, initializes time zones, converts local time to UTC
    Main
    Generates and sets initial login scene
    Report
    Represents report data, has count and detail strings
    ReportsController
    Controls the reports view by generating and populating all data within
    SchedulesController
    Controls and populates the schedules view which displays appointments for each Contact chosen through a dropdown
    User
    Represents a user
    UserController
    Controls and populates the users (login) view, controls allUsers array
